<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[96,1535,1860,2003]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[96,251,1861,1890]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[274,339,1860,1890]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
(length 7.3 mm). The specimen has the characteristic coloration described for the species, with legs light brown with darker rings and patches (
<figureCitation box="[978,1104,1898,1927]" captionStart="Figures 1―5" captionStartId="1.[96,188,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[97,1537,167,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-102@1.[795,1537,845,1722]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1―5. Eustiromastix falcatus Galiano male from Monte Alegre, Pará, Brazil. 1, Left palp proventral view. 2, Left palp retrolateral view. 3, Left palp ventral view. 4, Habitus dorsal view. 5, Habitus ventral view. Scale, figs. 1-3: 0.5 mm, figs. 4-5: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5092889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5092889/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figs. 4-5</figureCitation>
). Moreover, this resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1979" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1979" box="[296,506,1935,1965]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macropalpus">
<emphasis box="[296,506,1935,1965]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. macropalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from them in having the palp with a shorter embolus and a flattened tibial apophysys, wider than long, and a long and curved cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1257,1973,2003]" captionStart="Figures 1―5" captionStartId="1.[96,188,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[97,1537,167,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-102@1.[795,1537,845,1722]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1―5. Eustiromastix falcatus Galiano male from Monte Alegre, Pará, Brazil. 1, Left palp proventral view. 2, Left palp retrolateral view. 3, Left palp ventral view. 4, Habitus dorsal view. 5, Habitus ventral view. Scale, figs. 1-3: 0.5 mm, figs. 4-5: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5092889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5092889/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figs. 1-3</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano, M. E." box="[1285,1473,1973,2003]" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="216 - 218" refId="ref998" refString="Galiano, M. E. 1981. Three new species of Salticidae (Araneae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 176: 216 - 218." type="journal article" year="1981">Galiano 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
