<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[96,1535,1859,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[96,288,1866,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[307,426,1866,1895]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[445,635,1866,1896]" country="Trinidad and Tobago" name="Port of Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Port of Spain</collectingRegion>
), French Guiana (Saint-Élie, National Natural Reserve La Trinité) and 
<collectingCountry box="[158,240,1904,1933]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Pará). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1981" box="[361,663,1902,1932]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Eustiromastix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcatus">
<emphasis box="[361,663,1902,1932]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Eustiromastix falcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to date has only been found in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1240,1324,1904,1933]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. However, this species might be present throughout other Amazonian locations of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1225,1941,1970]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
or may be in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[96,236,1979,2008]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[248,349,1979,2008]" name="Guyana" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Guyana</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry box="[393,527,1979,2008]" name="Suriname" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Suriname</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[96,1533,173,240]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[96,261,173,202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the second published record of this species since the original description (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano, M. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="216 - 218" refId="ref998" refString="Galiano, M. E. 1981. Three new species of Salticidae (Araneae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 176: 216 - 218." type="journal article" year="1981">Galiano 1981</bibRefCitation>
), and the second location other than its 
<typeStatus box="[713,773,212,240]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
